I came in 15 minutes before my bus came expecting that must be more than enough time for them to make me an oatmeal to-go. There was one guy in front of me, and all he ordered was a coffee. By the time they started to make my food, which, for some reason, they needed to endlessly discuss about, I was already out of time; there were only 3 minutes left until the bus came, and it would take 25 minutes for the next one to arrive.  I told him I was waiting for the bus as a polite way of saying, “you’re way too god-damn slow, kiddo” and - because he understood it would take even more time - he gave me the receipt and told me to keep it “just in case”.  Well the bus came and I stepped out - without my oatmeal (or anything for dinner). I came home and called, asking for a refund. “It’s not our fault”, he said. “You didn’t give us enough time”.

Maybe not the best place to stop in for a fast coffee on your way to work, but they have an extensive menu (though I wish they had smoothies and juices like the other location) and again, are open 24/7!  Also, they are one of the only places that totally gets how to make a proper iced coffee, by dissolving the sugar in a little bit of hot coffee, and then mixing in ice and the iced coffee...their ice coffee got us through our move last summer, and I look forward to it now that it's getting warm out again.

After he got off the phone he asked me what did I want. I told him that I wanted a salad but I didn't know what toppings I asked if could go to the salad bar and place my order there. He said okay; as I was standing there no one came to me to ask what I wanted.  When I said whose going to take my order the same guy in the front told me I had to go back to the register.( Why did I have to go back and forth why couldn't you just tell me that in the beginning.) After that I place my order I waited another 20 minutes; in the midst of all of this there was no one else in the store, no potential customers. When I asked what was the hold up they told me that they had deliveries but I'm the only customer in the store so how can deliveries be more important than the customer service at the actual establishment. What makes  it even worse is that there  were people in the front just talking not working.  20 minutes passed and its not until I started complaining, the manager came out and said oh you placed your order at 8:21; but at this point it was already 8:40 and this is when they started my salad and had the audacity to try to rush my salad because I started complaining.  The customer service was terrible. They were very rude and I felt racially discriminated because when a Caucasian woman came into the store she immediately got service. Being from this neighborhood I support local business however I've noticed over  the past couple months and I can tell you the quality of service has declined since it's been established little over  a year ago. I will never return back don't go to Sunset bagels and their food is not even great.
